<br>
I wasn't online when Blayze was camping the zone and all this stuff went down and really haven't heard much about it in guild chat. Then i come and read this and I am saddened. The click stick would be nice to have around for sure. And i can say that if Blayze gets his hands on the rage drop a huge scheduled raid will take place to finish the epic. <br>
<br>
It is obvious to those of us who hunt in the same zones as AS that they are not looking to make many friends, they are rude and are a nonroleplaying guild on a roleplaying server. I would like to say that AS is not all bad though. Tonight a friend of mine made a wrong turn in Kael and ended up getting crushed in the arena. He was looking to find someway of retrieving it and in came a few AS guildies into Kael. Shayde tried to drag the corpse, after hearing my friends story, with no luck. But the intent to help was there.<br>
<br>
That being said I can certainly understand Blayze's frustration with AS. And sometimes its best to stand down, even when you can grab the prize, because a server this small can close up on you pretty quick. If i am grouped with Blayze and an AS member is LFG will he/she be invited into our group? Doesn't look like it. Keep that pattern of behavior up and you better hope you have a lot of people in your guild, because out of guild xp grouping will get harder and harder.<br>
